      "author": "heeeyMan",
      "description": "## Mobile conflict resolution, reworked\n\n- **Step-by-step conflict wizard** — conflicts are now resolved one file per screen with a progress indicator and Back/Next navigation, instead of one long scrolling list. Much easier when several files clash.\n- **Keyboard-aware on mobile** — the resolution dialog now stays above the on-screen keyboard (detected via Capacitor keyboard events and visualViewport), and the editor scrolls into view on focus, so the text field and the Resolve button are no longer hidden behind the keyboard. Respects the device status bar.\n- Applies to both the Git and GitHub API sync engines.\n\nAlso: tightened the Personal Access Token guidance (fine-grained scope + expiration) in the README and settings.\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/heeeyMan/ObsSync/compare/0.2.5...0.2.10",
